Reasoning: 
1. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - This paper deals with natural language processing tasks such as word segmentation and morphological tagging, which fall under the purview of cs.CL.
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The proposed model is an energy-based model that uses machine learning techniques to jointly solve the word segmentation and morphological tagging tasks.
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper proposes an AI-based approach to solve the word segmentation and morphological tagging tasks in Sanskrit.
4. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) - The paper uses neural network-based approaches to improve the performance of the proposed model.
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper discusses the use of graph-based parsing techniques to improve the performance of the proposed model, which falls under the purview of cs.DS.
